0.1     Oct 29, 2022
    Initial version

0.2     June 7, 2023
    - fixed message:
        "Found 1 messages with an invalid date out of total messages"
      to include intended total message count.
    - slight formatting change to usage (--help) message for -c/--config

0.3     July 15, 2023
    - spam-summary.plx:
        - can now decode subjects using UTF-8 encoding, so we no longer
          get subjects printed like:
            =?UTF-8?B?8J+SpUFUVEVOVElPTvCfkqUgM08uT09PIHdvcmx...
    - README.md, spam-summary.1:
        - removed example showing a subject of '=?utf-8?B?UGF5ZXogdm90c...'
          since we can now decode that UTF

0.4     Dec 28, 2024
    - spam-summary.plx:
        - fixed error with incorrect dates by including more error checking.
          It would crap out with messages like:
            Second '+0100' out of range 0..59 at /home/rj/bin/spam-summary ...
          when it encountered dates like:
            "7 Dec 10:03:04 +0100 ..."
          instead of dates like:
            "7 Dec 2024 10:03:04 +0100 ...", 
          and it interpreted +0100 incorrectly because of the missing year
    - README.UTF8-handling:
        - added

0.5     Aug 9, 2025:
    - spam-summary.plx:
        - massive improvement to figuring out date.
          No longer gets many warning messages such as:
            Use of uninitialized value $min in numeric gt (>) at ...
          for $min, $%hour, $sec, $month in dates like:  07-28-2025
          Tries to figure out dates of DD-DD-YYYY. Checks for nonsensical
          dates with that format to guess which of DD-MM-YYYY and MM-DD-YYYY.
          Checks if a future date.
        - process_message() is a new subroutine created to reduce duplicated
          code in handling the case of reaching EOF in the mailbox and then 
          having to process the last mail message.  So 2 calls to it from
          process_mailbox()
        - dprint() is now smarter and deals with potential binary in the message
          because of UTF-8 or whatever, and causing code to explode when used
          with double --debug options
        - figure_out_date() created to reduce clutter in process_mailbox(),
          particularly with the far greater amount of code dealing with dates
        - max_len_of_strings() created to reduce of duplicated code
        - decode_subject(0 has been changed to decode_line() since there is
          no reason it has to be a Subject.  Tries harder to figure out if
          the line passed to it is (valid) MIME-Header encoding, or UTF-8.
        - output now separates reporting for each folder with line of dashes
          to make it easier to read (I hope).
        - massive refactoring.  Better comments, messages, keeping within 80
          character line widths,
        - The --version option now also prints out which version of the
          Moxad:;Config module it is using.  eg:  spam-summary --version
            program version: 0.5
            Moxad::Config version: 0.0.9
